    <text>
        <body>
            <head>232. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in Morocco<note n="1"
                    place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d232fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                    Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 69, Morocco:
                    7/78–8/80. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact_1">Niact</gloss> Immediate; <gloss
                        target="#t_Exdis_1">Exdis</gloss>. Sent for information to Nouakchott,
                    Paris, and Madrid. Printed from a copy that was received in the White House
                    Situation Room. Drafted by <persName corresp="recoJB3QsHSMqYcVi"
                        >Bishop</persName>; cleared in <gloss target="#t_PM_1">PM</gloss>/SAS and
                        <gloss target="#t_AF_1">AF</gloss>/W; approved by <persName
                        corresp="reciS8viNYFKOFWI7">Draper</persName>. (National Archives, RG 59,
                    Central Foreign Policy File, D780384–0711)</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1978-09-20T23:46:00+00:00">September 20, 1978, 2346Z</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>239613. Subject: Moroccan Use of <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3QSbxhrMctVdHq">F–5
                    Aircraft</rs>.</p>
            <p>1. <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Department</orgName> believes that Moroccans
                and Algerians are again exploring possibility of a negotiated settlement to the <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recD8UEyBEWnzRQtf">Sahara conflict</rs>. We
                realize that before a settlement is in sight, or replacement aircraft are available,
                Moroccans are unlikely to withdraw <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3QSbxhrMctVdHq"
                    >F–5s</rs> currently stationed in Sahara. However, to remind King that this use
                of <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3QSbxhrMctVdHq">F–5s</rs> creates a serious problem
                in <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName>’s <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs>
                <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recsWOnchx3QJo5qE">relationship</rs> with U.S.,
                and thereby hopefully put some additional pressure on him to seek a political
                settlement to the dispute, Ambassador is requested to make following points during
                his farewell audience with <persName corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh"
                    >Hassan</persName>.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d232fn2">An unknown hand
                    placed a checkmark next to this sentence.</note>
            </p>
            <p>—U.S. understands <gloss target="#t_GOM_1">
                    <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">GOM</placeName>
                </gloss> continues to station <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3QSbxhrMctVdHq">F–5</rs>
                aircraft in Sahara. Given our disagreement regarding the consistency of this use of
                American supplied equipment with the terms of the 1960 <rs
                    type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recGwJdP0JlBPSbVG">U.S.-Moroccan military
                    assistance agreement</rs>, and the reluctance of Moroccan authorities to
                guarantee that <rs type="topic" corresp="recJ9z9SORjaCLZG1">military equipment</rs>
                to be purchased in the U.S. will not be employed for the defense of the Sahara, the
                U.S. has found it necessary to suspend action on requests for <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recYitJjr1dXM44FB">sales</rs> of most significant combat items.</p>
            <pb facs="0587" n="566" xml:id="pg_566"/>
            <p>—Time is fast approaching when <rs type="event" corresp="rec2z1tbfKZPT8edv"
                    >administration</rs> must inform <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM"
                    >Congress</orgName> there has been a violation of <rs
                    type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recGwJdP0JlBPSbVG">U.S.-Moroccan <rs
                        type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs>
                    agreement</rs>. It would be very helpful when giving this notification to be
                able to inform the <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> that some
                assurance had been received from the Moroccan Government regarding the eventual
                withdrawal of the <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3QSbxhrMctVdHq">F–5s</rs> from the
                Sahara. If the <rs type="event" corresp="rec2z1tbfKZPT8edv">administration</rs>
                cannot inform the <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> that some
                such assurance has been received, it is possible that even more serious problems
                could arise in our <rs type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military
                    assistance</rs>
                <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recsWOnchx3QJo5qE">relationship</rs>.</p>
            <p>—The <rs type="event" corresp="rec2z1tbfKZPT8edv">administration</rs> hopes it will
                be possible to reach some understanding on this issue prior to the King’s State
                    visit<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d232fn3">See <ref target="#d161">Document
                        161</ref>.</note> to avoid having it arise during the visit, when we would
                prefer that the emphasis be on the broad range of shared objectives and cooperation
                between <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName> and the U.S.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="rec9EBLnqQPcxRtYr">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Christopher</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
